The paper proposes a novel autoencoder architecture based on recurrent neural networks to generate compressed representations of multivariate time series (MTS), which may contain missing values and have variable lengths. The paper focuses on learning fixed-length vectorial representations, whose pairwise similarities are aligned with a kernel function that operates in input space and handles missing values. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel autoencoder architecture based on recurrent neural networks to generate compressed representations of MTS, which suggests that it belongs to the Machine Learning sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a framework for one-class classification and imputation of missing data in time series extracted from ECG signals, which suggests that it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence sub-category. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper proposes a novel autoencoder architecture based on recurrent neural networks, which suggests that it belongs to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing sub-category. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper focuses on learning compressed representations of MTS, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition sub-category.
